	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />PCE Engine had a really successful addon, and that is most probably the main reason for the MegaCD idea. Only difference is that NEC was pushing the CD instead of cards, while Sega did both CD and cart.<br />There is a very recent review at Sega-16 with one main figure at Sega during the 32X times and there is a lot of good info about why it made sense etc. In the end it still turned into a blunder... but it sold hundreds of thousands, unlike some other flops from others.<br />I do personally think there was no need for either, or the MegaCD should have had its own video out so the DMA to MD VDP VRAM for display bottleneck  gets eliminated, and in the process you can introduce fair bit of extra stuff as far as graphics go. <br /><br />You can do 512 color flat bitmaps with MegaCD though, using the CRAM DMA method I described earlier in this thread. MegaCD side is not halted for the duration of the DMA, so while MD side shows the bitmap, the MegaCD side can render next frame. Chilly Willy is cooking up something around it last time I spoke to him.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


